---
name: pgvector-17

dependencies:
  - postgres-17

# The `files:` entry below is a glob, not a pinned filename. This is a
# deliberate trade-off: a glob keeps pgvector version bumps cheap (bump
# config/blobs.yml and scripts/fetch-blobs.sh; the three pgvector-N
# specs don't need to be touched). The risk a glob normally invites —
# silently building against the wrong tarball if multiple match — is
# closed in the packaging script, which asserts exactly one match and
# fails loudly otherwise (see packages/pgvector-17/packaging,
# `extract_archive`). Reviewed in issue #2 item #28.
files:
  - pgvector/pgvector-*.tar.gz
